74.5	Stalker_(film)	Stalker (film)	Stalker (Russian: ) is a 1979 science fiction film directed by Andrei Tarkovsky, with a screenplay written by Boris and Arkady Strugatsky, loosely based on their novel Roadside Picnic. It depicts an expedition led by the Stalker to bring his two clients to a site known as the Zone, which has the supposed potential to fulfill a person's innermost desires.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/d/d4/Stalker_poster.jpg/220px-Stalker_poster.jpg
